Name: Rookie #78
Title: Trae Young 2018 Panini Prizm Rookie #78
Description: The Trae Young 2018-19 Panini Prizm Rookie is his most iconic base rookie card. As part of a remarkable 2018 NBA rookie class along with Luka Doncic, DeAndre Ayton, and Shai Gilgeous-Alexander, Trae is an exciting part of the NBA's future. Channeling Stephen Curry, Trae's game and playing style, centered on the three point shot, fits in seamlessly within the modern NBA. After a phenomenal second season where he scored and passed the ball at an extremely high level, Trae is an elite offensive player on a fast track to becoming one of the best point guards in recent memory. His Prizm rookie card is a great card to own going forward.

Name: Rookie #248
Title: Zion Williamson 2019 Panini Prizm Rookie #248
Description: The Zion Williamson 2019-20 Panini Prizm Rookie is the poster card for the hobby's resurgance during the 2019-20 NBA season. Similar to the base Prizm rookies of Ja Morant, Luka Doncic, Trae Young, and Jayson Tatum, Panini printed a plentiful amount of this one card. Only time will tell if this affects demand in the long haul, but if Zion lives up to the sky high expectations and claims the NBA's throne then watch out. Drafted #1 overall out of Duke University in the 2019 NBA Draft, Zion is easily the most explosive, talented, and dominant prospect to come out of college basketball within the last decade. His highlight dunks throw fans and the media into a frenzy, with many comparing Zion to a young LeBron James - should he be able to live up to the hype, this card will become a must-have staple in any collection.

Description: The Kobe Bryant 1996-97 Topps Rookie is one of the most recognizable base rookies cards of the 'Black Mamba'. In the 1996 NBA Draft, Kobe was selected 13th overall by the Charlotte Hornets straight out of Lower Merion High School in Philadelphia but was subsequently traded to the Los Angeles Lakers on draft night. For the next two decades, Kobe played the game of basketball with unmatched intensity and dedication, winning five championships and one NBA MVP award among other accolades, becoming a cultural icon. Playing alongside Shaquille O'Neal and Paul Gasol at different points of his career, while echoeing the playing style of Michael Jordan, Kobe created an everlasting legacy for himself on the court. Off the court, Kobe was a global ambassador for the sport, successful in business as an investor,  and even won an Oscar for one of his many creative masterpieces post-retirement.

Title: 2020 Yu-Gi-Oh! TCG Phantom Rage 1st Edition Booster Box
Description: The 2020 Yu-Gi-Oh! TCG Phantom Rage 1st Edition Booster Box released on November 6, 2020, and comes with 9 cards per pack and 24 packs per box. Ghosts from the past return to the fray in November’s Phantom Rage booster set! Phantom Rage doesn’t just remaster popular themes from the past, it unites them as well. You can find new Phantom Knight and Raidraptor cards, but you can also find new cards that are Phantom Knights AND Raidraptors! You can play these cards in their own Decks, but you can also create your own hybrid Deck that takes the best of each theme to max out your Xyz Summoning power. You can also find a new theme based on Fusion Summoning that excels at performing consecutive Fusion Summons. Normally, to Fusion Summon you need to use a Spell Card for each Fusion Summon you perform along with multiple separate cards to use as materials, but this brand-new theme is anchored by a powerful Spell Card that Summons up to 5 Tokens you can use for Fusion Summoning... and then lets you Fusion Summon twice consecutively! What else can you expect from Phantom Rage? How about… - 17 World Premiere cards, the most ever in a single booster set! - The long-awaited crossover between "U.A." and "F.A."! - New Ritual, Fusion, Synchro, Xyz, and Link Monsters! - More cards to enhance strategies introduced in Rise of the Duelist! - And more! The Phantom Rage booster set contains 100 new cards: 50 Commons, 26 Super Rares, 14 Ultra Rares, and 10 Secret Rares.

Name: 1st Edition Booster Box 2X Lot
Title: 2020 Yu-Gi-Oh! TCG Phantom Rage 1st Edition Booster Box 2X Lot
Description: The 2020 Yu-Gi-Oh! TCG Phantom Rage 1st Edition Booster Box released on November 6, 2020, and comes with 9 cards per pack and 24 packs per box. Ghosts from the past return to the fray in November’s Phantom Rage booster set! Phantom Rage doesn’t just remaster popular themes from the past, it unites them as well. You can find new Phantom Knight and Raidraptor cards, but you can also find new cards that are Phantom Knights AND Raidraptors! You can play these cards in their own Decks, but you can also create your own hybrid Deck that takes the best of each theme to max out your Xyz Summoning power. You can also find a new theme based on Fusion Summoning that excels at performing consecutive Fusion Summons. Normally, to Fusion Summon you need to use a Spell Card for each Fusion Summon you perform along with multiple separate cards to use as materials, but this brand-new theme is anchored by a powerful Spell Card that Summons up to 5 Tokens you can use for Fusion Summoning... and then lets you Fusion Summon twice consecutively! What else can you expect from Phantom Rage? How about… - 17 World Premiere cards, the most ever in a single booster set! - The long-awaited crossover between "U.A." and "F.A."! - New Ritual, Fusion, Synchro, Xyz, and Link Monsters! - More cards to enhance strategies introduced in Rise of the Duelist! - And more! The Phantom Rage booster set contains 100 new cards: 50 Commons, 26 Super Rares, 14 Ultra Rares, and 10 Secret Rares.
